          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Model Overview and Distillation Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LTX-2 19B Distilled FP8 is a 19-billion-parameter model distilled from a larger predecessor, using FP8 (8-bit floating-point) quantization to reduce memory footprint and accelerate inference. Key advantages include lower latency and reduced hardware costs, making it suitable for high-throughput API services. The distillation process preserves core model accuracy while enhancing efficiency, enabling deployment on GPUs with limited VRAM."
          }
